  "text": "A question from Jim that states, I think I have penetrated the mystery of my lifelong anger and make some mistakes. I think I've always been aware subconsciously of my ability to master new learnings, but my desire to successfully complete my mission on Earth has been energized by the error and group and derivation and destructive anger when I fail. Would you comment on this observation? I am Ra we would suggest that as this entity is aware of its position as a wanderer, it may also consider what pre incarnative decisions it undertook to make regarding the a personal or self-oriented portion of the choosing to be here at this particular time space. But potential for what? This is the pre incarnative question. The work of sixth density is to unify wisdom and compassion. This entity abounds in wisdom the compassion. In the more conscious being, this expires or manifests itself as lack of a compassion for self.",
